Further, define di to be the distance of county i from the boundary, with di
> 0 and di
< 0 for counties north and south of the boundary, respectively. Let f (·) and g(·), with g(di) = 0 for di
< 0, be smooth functions that represent other factors (besides the heating policy) that affect nonlabor income and are correlated with distance. We then replace Eq. (10) with the GRD model of the age at first marriage as a function of the heating policy:11\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
